1.title: Introductions

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

1.plot: Investigator Johanna Leoni introduces the various people who help shape the organization.

2.title: Introduction to UFOs

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

2.plot: Investigator Johanna Leoni defines and discuss the subject of UFOs.

3.title: Close Encounters

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

3.plot: Johanna and investigator Murray Douglas examine the system of categorizing UFO incidents. They examine a few sightings that are classified as CE-1 (Close Encounters of the First Kind.)

4.title: Squawker Sightings

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

4.plot: Squawker is a half man, bird-like creature that stands about six feet tall, who seems is to scare the local folks. Squawker is the name given to the creature by those very locals because of the sounds that it reportedly made.

5.title: Mysterious Aircraft

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

5.plot: In this episode we take a historical look at X-planes and famous UFO sightings. Is there a connection between experimental aircraft and certain UFO incidents?

6.title: Pilots & The Unkown

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

6.plot: CUPIC investigator Gavin Leoni examines cases that involve pilots and their encounters with the unknown.

7.title: CE3 Contact

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

7.plot: An examination of subtle and open contact with the unknown. Close Encounters of the Third Kind.

8.title: McAllister Affair

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

8.plot: Johanna and Gavin presents the story of the McAllister Affair, featuring case # 0071990-Raphael, The Contact.

9.title: Alien Abductions

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

9.plot: Johanna Leoni and Dr. Ruth Marx examines reports of Abductions.

10.title: End of Introductions

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

10.plot: Inside the CUPIC organization. The introductions are over, it's time for some serious investigating. Season 1 Finale.

1.title: Sky Watchers

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

1.plot: Johanna has taken a temporary assignment in Hawaii, leaving Sandra and Gavin in charge of CUPIC-Arizona. They both talk about the growing case load in front of them.

2.title: The Apparition

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

2.plot: CUPIC investigation are not just limited to UFO encounters. Sandra talks about the cases of other paranormal events that this organization investigates.

3.title: Probing Inquiry

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

3.plot: Previously, we examined the wide scope of cases that CUPIC will investigate. We are about to present is one particular subject that this organization will not ad to their to do list, despite the insistence of a sibling duo.

4.title: Ghostly Encounters

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

4.plot: Sandra investigate a few of the cases that have recently flooded the organization involving ghostly entities.

5.title: Angels & Fastwalkers

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

5.plot: Sandra and Gavin discuss UFO sightings by both visual and radar observation.

6.title: Roadside Assistance

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

6.plot: Gavin presents the case of a Father driving his daughter home on a lonely road between towns during the early evening hours. The two have a bizarre experience during their journey in the twilight.

7.title: Little Children

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

7.plot: Sandra and Gavin study reports of strange Black Eyed Children showing up on eyewitness properties, making odd requests.

8.title: The Visitors

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

8.plot: As they continues to sort through the reports, Sandra come across an incident involving a local girl and a strange intruder. Tyler introduces a new member of the organization to Sandra who turns out to be a familiar face.

9.title: The Emissary

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

9.plot: Sandra has her meeting with Merona, while Gavin continues to sort through reports. He finds an interesting story about a man who has an interesting encounter at a local park.

10.title: Black and White

episode of.title: CUPIC: Diary of an Investigator (TV Series 2011– )

10.plot: Gavin meets Bob Merona and he gives him a wealth of information about the recent sightings of mysterious triangular shaped flying objects and sonic booms. Bob arranges for Gavin to meet a contact who worked at Area 51. Sandra travels to Sedona to meet someone with information about the recent cases of mystery surveillance.

imdb.plot outline: Members of the Arizona chapter of CUPIC (kyu-pik): Central Unidentified Phenomenon Investigation Committee, a private organization, investigate reports of the unknown. Their goal is to find a scientific and logical explanation for these cases, but each of them soon realize that it will not to be an easy task.
